annotationA: Zinc transporter 35C is involved in cellular and organismal zinc efflux and plays a major role in the detoxification of zinc excess. The gene is a target of the metal-responsive transcription factor MTF-1
annotationB: Zinc/iron regulated transporter-related protein 71B, isoform B; Metal ion transmembrane transporter activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: metal ion transport; transmembrane transport
